  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail profile picture, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to your Google Account:**\n   - Open a web browser and go to [your Google Account](https://myaccount.google.com).\n   - If you're not already signed in, log in with your Gmail credentials.\n\n2. **Navigate to Personal Info:**\n   - Once you're in your Google Account, look for the \"Personal info\" section, usually found on the left-hand side navigation menu.\n\n3. **Access your Profile Picture:**\n   - Under \"Profile,\" you'll see your profile picture. Click on it.\n\n4. **Remove your Profile Picture:**\n   - You might see an option to \"Remove\" your current profile picture. If so, click on it to remove the photo.\n   - If there's no clear \"Remove\" option, you might need to upload a blank or generic image as a workaround since Google occasionally changes the interface and options available.\n\n5. **Confirm Changes:**\n   - Follow any additional prompts to confirm your changes and ensure that your profile picture is removed or changed to a default image.\n\nAfter completing these steps, check your Gmail and other Google services to ensure that your profile picture has been updated across all platforms. Keep in mind that changes might take a little while to propagate through all Google services.",
